cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as video reconstruction, object segmentation, and pose tracking, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for unsupervised learning, which could also place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of per-pixel filters and the multigrid coarse-to-fine modeling strategy may also suggest a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also deals with video processing, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the mention of shared weights and compact models may suggest a connection to the cs.RO (Robotics) category, as these are important considerations in robotics applications.
